An '''auxiliary ego''', also known as simply an auxiliary, is the position taken by other participants in a [[role-playing]] exercise, or [[psychodrama]], in order to simulate particular situations for the [[protagonist]]s. As role-playing can include more than one protagonist, each may be operating in the role of auxiliary ego to each other as the exploration of each role changes with the entrance of new situations. The director of the role-play, often a [[teacher]] or counselor, can also be an auxiliary and typically is when clients are in the position of protagonist.
